commit.message:
src/headers/daemon.h: avoid redefinition of 'last_selection_time'

Noticed build failure on gcc-10 as:

```
gcc  -L/home/slyfox/dev/git/gpm/src  -o gpm mice.o ... report.o tools.o   -lm
ld: twiddler.o:gpm/src/headers/daemon.h:183:
  multiple definition of `last_selection_time'; mice.o:gpm/src/headers/daemon.h:183: first defined here
ld: synaptics.o:git/gpm/src/headers/daemon.h:183:
  multiple definition of `last_selection_time'; mice.o:git/gpm/src/headers/daemon.h:183: first defined here
```

gcc-10 will change the default from -fcommon to fno-common:
https://gcc.gnu.org/PR85678.

The error also happens if CFLAGS=-fno-common passed explicitly.

Signed-off-by: Sergei Trofimovich <slyfox@gentoo.org>

Merge pull request #10 from vapier/master

misc warning cleanups
clean up a few unused funcs/vars

report/oops: add attributes to mark as printf functions

This allows gcc to do printf checking on calls to these funcs to make
sure they're being called correctly.
update ignored file list

report: avoid -Wformat-security warnings

Some functions warn when you pass a string to a printf style function
that is a dynamic buffer as its contents cannot be verified.  Since we
don't want to support that here, just use %s.
report/oops: constify format strings

Merge pull request #5 from dimkr/master

musl support
Added musl support to libgpm and the daemon.

Resolve linking against ncursesw

The NCURSES library ships with wide-character (UTF-8) version of
libncurses, the wide-character file is called ncursesw.so*. Check if
it is present and link against it.

Install unversioned solibrary

Unversioned solibraries are shipped with -devel packages in Linux
distros. Generate and install it for the consistency.
fix your damn email address, nico

if you're using strlen() on it, as we are in tp_serial_send_cmd(), it had better be a plain char. make it so, killing one warning. no reason to sprintf() into an unsigned char buffer, so make it not, killing the other. this cleans all warnings from synaptic.c using gcc 3.7.2
